---
title: Cranberry Thyme Chicken with Roasted Brussels Sprouts, Carrots & Onion
description: Can you feel it yet? Fall in the air: earthy smells and sweater-weather temps. It’s thyme (see what we did there?) for the likes of cranberries and roasted root veggies! This chicken may seem like your basic cutlet, but dress it up with a jammy cranberry glaze, and you’ve got a sweet-sour-rich main dish, plus a crispy-edged, tender red onion, Brussels, and carrots side, making it a cozy meal for any night of the week–thank you, autumn!
